HEADWORD: Pluvise
<hw>Plu`vi`⟦ocir⟧se"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Pluvious</er>.]</ety> <def>The fifth month of the French republican
calendar adopted in 1793. It began January 20, and ended February 18.
See <er>Vend⟦eacute⟧miaire</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

